A SendGrid MCP server is an implementation of the Model Context Protocol that allows AI agents to interact with the SendGrid v3 API [1][2]. It enables agents to send transactional emails, manage dynamic templates, perform contact CRUD operations, analyze performance metrics, and handle suppression lists [1][3][4].

To configure the server in your MCP client, provide your SendGrid API key via environment variables [1][3][5]. For example, in a standard client configuration:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "sendgrid": {
      "command": "sendgrid-mcp",
      "env": {
        "SENDGRID_API_KEY": "SG.your_api_key_here",
        "READ_ONLY": "true"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Most implementations default to read-only mode to prevent accidental data changes [1][3][4]. Depending on the specific server version used, write operations may require explicit opt-in via environment variables or runtime approval tokens [1][3][6]. Multiple independent implementations are available in the open-source community [1][3][7][6][5][8].
